added: In the third quarter of 2020, Harrison raised $57 million, the largest quarterly total by a U.S. Senate candidate ever, breaking [[Beto O'Rourke]]'s record in the [[2018 United States Senate election in Texas|2018 Texas election]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Arkin |first=James |date=October 11, 2020 |title=Jaime Harrison shatters Senate fundraising record for South Carolina race |url=https://www.politico.com/news/2020/10/11/jaime-harrison-shatters-senate-fundraising-record-for-south-carolina-race-428541 |work=[[POLITICO]] |access-date=October 11, 2020}}</ref> He has also raised the most ever by a U.S. Senate candidate, beating another of O'Rourke's records.<ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Jaime Harrison sets Senate fundraising record in race against Lindsey Graham |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2020/oct/11/jaime-harrison-shatters-senate-fundraising-record-race-against-lindsey-graham |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=October 11, 2020 |access-date=October 11, 2020}}</ref>
